https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2017/09/android-8-0-oreo-thoroughly-reviewed/4/
The goal of locking down background processing is not only improve battery life but also to better manage memory 
so the device runs more smoothly

No more wakelocks, no silent background services
In Android parlance, this is a "wakelock"—an single app's ability to keep the phone awake to do processing work.
AnAdroid 8.0 is clamping down on wakelocks—an app's wakelocks will be automatically released by the system when the app is "idle." 
